            "description": "Two-loop integral family for mixed QCD-EW corrections to $gg \\to H$ at $\\mathcal{O}(g^3 g_s^2)$, where the Higgs couples to a top quark. This family depends only on $s$ and $m_t$, and evaluates to multiple polylogarithms with symbol alphabet $\\{x, 1+x, 1-x\\}$ after the rationalization $s/m_t^2 = 4x^2/(x^2-1)$. Contains 10 master integrals computed through $\\mathcal{O}(\\varepsilon^2)$ (weight 6). Boundary conditions fixed at $s \\to 0$ using regularity and the method of regions. Top-level topology is a hexagonal two-loop graph with 5 massive ($m_t$) edges and 1 massless internal line.",
